libemodbus
------------------------------------------
This library depends on libemodbus (uses ring buffer implementation). Emodbus
is capable of modbus datastructures parsing. Once the structure is parsed and
confirmed to be valid, the library calls your callback, passing parsed version
of request or response.

Runtime requirements:
  CUnit-2.1.3-1
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.212.g6af8fea4bbad
  libccontainer0-1.0.1+git20190103-1bl1
  libemodbus-devel-1.0.0+git20150528-1bl1
  libemodbus0-1.0.0+git20150528-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  CUnit-2.1.3-1
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libccontainer-devel-1.0.1+git20190103-1bl1
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/snegovick/libemodbus

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/snegovick/libemodbus.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libemodbus-1.0.0+git20150528-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libemodbus-1.0.0+git20150528-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libemodbus-1.0.0+git20150528-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libemodbus-1.0.0+git20150528-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libemodbus0-1.0.0+git20150528-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libemodbus-devel-1.0.0+git20150528-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libemodbus)
  /usr/bin/emodbus.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libemodbus.README
  /usr/share/doc/libemodbus/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libemodbus/README.md

(libemodbus0)
  /usr/bin/cygemodbus-0.dll

(libemodbus-devel)
  /usr/include/emodbus_parser.h
  /usr/lib/libemodbus.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libemodbus.pc

